Siemens Mulls Buyouts for Infrastructure Unit, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-12T00:35:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/siemens-mulls-buyouts-for-infrastructure-unit-ft-says-correct-.html
(Corrects position of Busch in first paragraph.)  Siemens AG (SIE)  may consider making
acquisitions to strengthen its Infrastructure and Cities unit
and accelerate expansion, the Financial Times reported, citing
Roland Busch, head of the company’s new business arm.  “Our goal is to grow faster than the market and faster
than our competitors,” Busch said, according to the FT. “Over
the course of time an acquisition is clearly possible,” he
said, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 